    "summaries": {
        "README.md": "The file is a comprehensive documentation of a Deep Packet Inspection (DPI) engine project, which is a software system that examines the contents of network packets as they pass through a checkpoint. Here's a summary:\n\n**Overview**\n\nThe DPI engine reads network captures, parses protocol headers, extracts domain names from TLS and HTTP, and applies blocking rules based on IP, app, or domain. It can run in simple (single-threaded) or multi-threaded modes.\n\n**Components**\n\n1. `pcap_reader`: Reads network captures and extracts packet data.\n2. `packet_parser`: Parses protocol headers (Ethernet, IP, TCP, UDP) and extracts relevant information.\n3. `sni_extractor`: Extracts domain names from TLS and HTTP packets.\n4. `types`: Defines data structures and functions for working with packets and flows.\n5. `dpi_engine`: The main orchestrator that manages the flow of packets through the system.\n\n**Flow**\n\n1. Read PCAP file: The DPI engine reads a PCAP file containing network capture data.\n2. Parse packets: Each packet is parsed to extract protocol headers and other relevant information.\n3. Extract SNI: Domain names are extracted from TLS and HTTP packets.\n4. Apply blocking rules: Packets are dropped or forwarded based on IP, app, or domain blocking rules.\n5. Generate report: A report is generated showing the number of packets processed, dropped, and forwarded, as well as application breakdown and detected domain names.\n\n**Multi-threaded Version**\n\nThe multi-threaded version uses a producer-consumer pattern, where:\n\n1. Reader threads read PCAP files and push packets to a queue.\n2. Load balancer threads distribute packets to fast path threads.\n3. Fast path threads process packets and apply blocking rules.\n4. Output writer threads write processed packets to an output file.\n\n**Extending the Project**\n\nThe documentation suggests several ideas for improving the project, including adding more app signatures, bandwidth throttling, live statistics dashboard, QUIC/HTTP3 support, and persistent rules.\n\nOverall, the DPI engine project is a complex software system that demonstrates network protocol parsing, deep packet inspection, flow tracking, and multi-threaded architecture."
    },
